Description
-----------

The date tag is used to display the current time in a specific format
(the format of Ruby's inbuilt method [Time#strftime][1]). Have a look a
the examples below to see some possible outputs.

[1]: http://www.ruby-doc.org/core/classes/Time.html


Examples
--------

<table class="examples">
<tr>
  <th>Usage</th><th>Output</th>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>\{date:}</td>
  <td>{date:}</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>\{date: {format: %Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S}}</td>
  <td>{date: {format: %Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S}}</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>\{date: {format: %x - %X}}</td>
  <td>{date: {format: %x - %X}}</td>
</tr>
</table>
